name: NonPharmacologicTreatmentsForChronicPain
title: Non pharmacologic treatments for chronic pain
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This grouped value set contains codes representing evidence-based interventions, therapies, procedures and treatments which may be useful for the treatment of chronic pain. It does not include medications.),(Data Element Scope: This value set contains ICD10-PCS, SNOMED-CT, and NCI codes representing treatments for chronic pain that have undergone evaluation in rigorous systematic reviews. It includes procedures, therapies and treatments. Most high-level treatments were identified in the Cochrane database as of December 2017 (e.g., yoga, PT). This value set does not include medications.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing treatments for chronic pain (including procedures, therapies and treatments). Most high-level treatments were identified in the Cochrane database as of December 2017 (e.g., chiropractic therapy). Descendants/children of each high-level treatment are also included (e.g., chiropractic manipulation of cervical region).),(Exclusion Criteria: Medications used to treat chronic pain and codes representing Observed Entities.)
